{
  "abstract": "Pearl Millet rust, caused by Puccinia penniseti, has great destructive potential and is reported to occur in Africa and in Asia.  There are several locations in India where rust is frequently severe, though the disease generally comes late in the season and thus is unlikely to cause significant yield reduction... ",
